#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "简介"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:9
msgid ""
"Rigging makes animation possible. Without a good rig animation is incredibly "
"frustrating. Imagine animating a bouncing ball without the ability to squash "
"it against the ground? Try animating a monkey swinging through the trees "
"with no control to make the monkey's hands grab onto the branches. What if "
"you had to animate an army tank speeding through the desert by positioning "
"each tread on the tank one at a time?"
msgstr ""
"绑定让动画成为可能。没有一个好的绑定的动画是难于让人信服的。想象一下弹跳小球"
"在击中地面时没有一个压缩的动画？一个猴子在树上荡漾而手没有抓在树枝上的动画。"
"如果你要制作一个军用坦克加速通过沙漠的动画，你将不得不每次都一个一个的调整坦"
"克履带上的每个踏板来完成这个动画？"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:17
msgid ""
"At its most basic level, rigging solves motion problems. Imagine a door that "
"opens into a hallway. Without a rig, the door will not swing open properly "
"(1). A rig is needed to help the door swing open on its hinges (2, 3, 4), "
"and there are many ways to rig the door. Door 2 gets rigged by repositioning "
"the :term:`Object Origin` of the door. Door 3 gets rigged by :term:"
"`Parenting` the door to an :term:`Empty`. Door 4 gets rigged by :term:"
"`Weight Painting` all of its :term:`Vertices` to a :term:`Bone` in an :term:"
"`Armature`."
msgstr ""
"绑定在最基本的层面上解决了运动问题。想象一扇通向走廊的门。没有一个绑定的门不"
"能正常打开(如门1)。需要一个绑定来帮助门沿着其铰链打开(如门2、3、4),有很多方法"
"可以绑定门。门2获得通过门的物体“ :term:`Object Origin` 原点”来绑定。门 3通过"
"将 :term:`空物体` 作为门的 :term:`父级` 物体来绑定。门 4通过 :term:`权重绘制"
"` 将门的所有 :term:`顶点` 指定给一个 :term:`骨架` 上的一个 :term:`骨骼` 来绑"
"定。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:27
msgid ""
"Most production rigs are more complicated than a simple door, but be careful "
"not to rush off building complicated rigs until you have developed some "
"experience. Rigging is a discipline that takes practice. Start by building "
"simple rigs (like a bouncing ball, a tumbling box, an odometer, a clock). "
"Stay humble. Stay patient. Study the fundamental concepts that make a "
"bouncing ball bounce. Add one rigging tool to your toolbox at a time. Test "
"your simple rigs in actual animation projects. And only after much trial and "
"error, consider putting everything together into the sophisticated character "
"rig of your dreams."
msgstr ""
"大多数的产品绑定比一个简单的门绑定更复杂，但要注意直到你有了一些经验之前不要"
"匆忙建造复杂的绑定。绑定是一门需要不断实践的学科。先从简单的绑定开始（像弹跳"
"的小球，滚筒、里程表、时钟）。保持点谦虚。保持点耐心。研究弹跳球反弹的基本概"
"念。一次在你的工具箱中添加一个绑定工具。在实际的动画项目中测试你的简单的绑"
"定。只有经过反复试验和错误，考虑把所有的学到的东西运用到你的梦想中的复杂的角"
"色绑定。"

#: ../../manual/rigging/introduction.rst:39
msgid ""
"The content of this chapter is simply a reference to how rigging is "
"accomplished in Blender. It should be paired with additional resources such "
"as Nathan Vegdahl's excellent (and free!) introduction to the fundamental "
"concepts of character rigging, `Humane Rigging <https://www.youtube.com/"
"playlist?list=PL3wFcRXImVPOQpi-wi7uriXBkykXVUntv>`__."
msgstr ""
"本章的内容是如何在Blender中完成绑定的简单的一个参考。应该搭配额外的资源，如"
"Nathan Vegdahl优秀（免费！）的介绍角色绑定的基本概念 `Humane Rigging教程 "
"<https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL3wFcRXImVPOQpi-"
"wi7uriXBkykXVUntv>`__。"
